n  it became an international fullservice banking group it is listed through its holding company crédit agricole sa on euronext paris’ first market and is part of the cac  stock market index in  the crédit agricole group reported revenues of € billion it was the title sponsor of the crédit agricole professional road cycling team from  to  contents  history  birth of crédit agricole and creation of the local and regional banks     building nationwide coverage     postwar period and creation of fédération nationale du crédit agricole     birth of a universal bank     institutional changes     crédit agricole in the st century  picking up the pace of business diversification     business overview  crédit agricole and the    crisis  getting back to fundamentals from   corporate governance  local banks  regional banks  fédération nationale du crédit agricole  crédit agricole sa  brand identity  slogan  visual identity  financial and market data  crédit agricole group data  crédit agricole sa group data  sports sponsorship  cycling  rugby  controversies  see also  references  external links historyedit source for most of the history section in the second half of the th century french farmers struggled to obtain longterm flexible reasonablypriced credit there were several attempts to set up farming banks including crédit foncier de france in  but none was successful birth of crédit agricole and creation of the local and regional banks   edit jules méline spearheaded the creation of the first local banks crédit agricole can trace its history back to the end of the th century and specifically to the act of  establishing the freedom of professional association which authorised among other things the creation of farm unions and the foundation of local mutual banks société de crédit agricole was created on  february  at salinslesbains in the district of poligny in the jura region it was the first of its kind in france drawing on this experience and in an effort to promote lending to small family farms the act of  november  which had the support of minister for agriculture jules méline paved the way for the creation of crédit agricole’s local banks the first local banks were set up by local elites including agronomists teachers and property owners with farmers playing a minority role in the early years business was made up exclusively of shortterm loans provided as advances on harvests enabling farmers to live more comfortably mediumterm and longterm loans were added later making it possible to buy equipment and livestock the  act did not confer any financial advantages and the local banks soon faced financial problems such as a lack of capital and insufficient collateral from small farmers it was not until  that the government addressed these problems by requiring the banque de france to provide funding to crédit agricole through an endowment of  million gold francs and an annual fee of  million francs a year later the act of  resolved the collateral issues meanwhile the act of  march  instituted a commission within the ministry for agriculture to distribute the government advances between the regional banks which were also created at this time these cooperative entities brought together the local banks in their catchment area and acted as their clearing organisations building nationwide coverage   edit more and more local and regional banks were established from the turn of the century by the eve of the first world war every region had at least one but the government continued to provide threequarters of the funding and shortterm lending still accounted for the lion’s share of business despite the authorisation to issue longterm loans granted by the acts of  december  and  march  with some regions becoming isolated owing to the war the need for a central bank to regulate business became more apparent especially as crédit agricole was asked to provide financing to rebuild farming operations damaged during the conflict in the s the bank continued to build its nationwide coverage and expand its business activities notably by introducing loans to smallscale rural craftsmen in  financing rural electrification and financing local authorities in rural areas from  the act of  august  gave greater independence to what was at that time a credit department reporting directly to the ministry for agriculture and established a public central clearing organisation for the regional banks the office national de crédit agricole was thus set up with louis tardy as its chief executive officer in  the institution was renamed caisse nationale de crédit agricole cnca and crédit agricole’s institutional structure was complete the  act also established the legal framework for crédit agricole’s operations in france local and regional banks did not emerge from the  crisis unscathed the caisse nationale took on a greater role and aided the most heavily exposed banks a joint deposit guarantee fund was set up in  the following year crédit agricole provided additional support by financing wheat stocks through discounting when the national cereals board onic was established the payment mechanisms used helped to make cheques and bank accounts more popular in the countryside between  and  the vichy regime imposed stricter state supervision on crédit agricole major financial developments also took place at this time including the creation of the fiveyear note postwar period and creation of fédération nationale du crédit agricole   edit to finance the postwar reconstruction effort and encourage the mechanisation of farming cnca stepped up deposittaking to supplement the funds provided by the government the regional banks opened many offices with the total increasing from  in  to  by  fédération nationale du crédit agricole fnca was created in  it was tasked with representing the crédit agricole regional banks with respect to the public authorities and cnca it also played a role in training staff and gradually expanding crédit agricole’s expertise in  crédit agricole was authorised by decree to finance property loans for primary residences in rural areas irrespective of the status of the owner even nonfarmers the distribution of longterm bonds created in  enabled crédit agricole to be selffinancing from  financial flows between the government and the organisation reversed with crédit agricole now sending deposits to the treasury crédit agricole continued to modernise with an influx of new managerial talent both in the regional banks and at cnca in  paul driant became the first chairman of cnca to come from a farming background he remained in this position for  years birth of a universal bank   edit in  as part of efforts to boost savings and remove crédit agricole from its budget the government gave cnca financial autonomy savings inflows no longer passed through the treasury and cnca was now responsible for balancing the surpluses and deficits of the regional banks the  rurality act extended crédit agricole’s potential financing sources to rural zones and to new types of customers such as craftsmen and food producers lending to smes and midtier firms followed after the banking reform of  allowed the organisation to offer households the same products as those provided by competitors including passbook accounts and home savings plans the first subsidiaries were set up at the end of the s to address the specific needs of cnca union d’études et d’investissements ui was created in  to make equity investments followed by segespar for asset management in  and unicrédit to grant loans to food producers in  crédit agricole began distributing home purchase savings products from  governmentregulated mortgages from  and firsttimebuyer loans in  in  the group adopted the slogan le bon sens près de chez vous common sense close to home crédit agricole opened its first foreign branch in chicago in  signalling the start of its strategy of international expansion in that year the banker magazine ranked crédit agricole among the world’s leading banks reflecting this progress crédit agricole was made subject to france’s  banking act previously it had been subject only to the rural code in addition an interbank agreement was signed to make crédit agricole bank cards part of the carte bleue system used by other banks the group’s business diversification started in the s the predica life insurance subsidiary was set up in  while property  casualty unit pacifica was created in  the group expanded into bancassurance offering the first retirement savings plans at this time many local bank directors were also directors of groupama an insurer from the farming sector there was talk of a merger between the two but this did not ultimately come to pass institutional changes   edit on  january  the cnca privatisation act came into force cnca was transformed into a public limited company with a  stake sold to the regional banks and  to staff crédit agricole became fully independent of the government putting an end to the latter’s practice of skimming off surplus funds in  crédit agricole lost the monopoly on granting lowinterest loans to farmers and one year later in  the normalisation process was completed as it was allowed to begin financing large corporations international expansion continued with the acquisition of stakes in banco ambrosiano veneto in italy in  and banco espirito santo in portugal in  consolidation among the regional banks began officially in  with the aim of reducing costs the aim was to halve the number of regional banks and that objective had been surpassed by the turn of the st century meanwhile  of the  regional banks were listed on the secondary market through issues of cooperative investment certificates although most of the share capital of the regional banks remained in the hands of the  million client stakeholders in  lucien douroux who led the plan to privatise fnca became cnca’s first chief executive officer having been appointed by crédit agricole from existing staff in  the group bought indosuez and then created indocam an asset management subsidiary renamed crédit agricole asset management in  and crédit agricole indosuez for corporate and investment banking in  diversification continued as the group took a stake in the newly privatised crédit lyonnais and acquired leading consumer finance company sofinco cnca was listed on the stockmarket in  under the name crédit agricole sa this gave the regional banks a listed vehicle through which to carry out major acquisitions crédit agricole in the st centuryedit this article contains content that is written like an advertisement please help improve it by removing promotional content and inappropriate external links and by adding encyclopedic content written from a neutral point of view august  learn how and when to remove this template message picking up the pace of business diversification   edit the headquarters of crédit lyonnais which was acquired by the crédit agricole group in  the st century saw the group continue to diversify its business lineup finaref was acquired in  that same year crédit agricole acquired crédit lyonnais in a friendly takeover orchestrated by then chairman of the board rené carron after a market battle was triggered by the government’s decision to auction off its stake in crédit lyonnais in december  the two banks were combined in  and  which led to the different business lines being grouped into subsidiaries this included the creation of calyon in  from the merger of the corporate and investment banking activities of crédit lyonnais and crédit agricole indosuez crédit lyonnais focused on retail banking and was rebranded as lcl in august  between  and  the regional banks and crédit agricole sa embarked on a major development plan aimed at bolstering the regional banks’ leading positions in france by gaining a greater presence in major cities while at the same time increasing the group’s international reach businesses were established in egypt ukraine serbia greece italy and portugal in  crédit agricole assurances was created to bring together the pacifica and predica brands in  the group starting to part away from newly formed italian banking giant intesa sanpaolo which crédit agricole was the largest shareholder of banca intesa despite on  january  crédit agricole still acted as the third largest shareholder of intesa sanpaolo on  march  crédit agricole acquired  former banca intesa branches as well as cariparma and friuladria from intesa sanpaolo in  crédit agricole acquired carispezia from intesa sanpaolo as well as  branches directly from intesa sanpaolo in  crédit agricole finally sold all the shares of intesa sanpaolo business overviewedit the group’s acquisitions enabled it to strengthen its leadership in french retail banking expand its position in corporate and investment banking and build up its international network of branches and subsidiaries by now the group was the numberone bank in france with  of the domestic market the global numbertwo by revenues and numberten by profits according to fortune magazine and number worldwide according to forbes rankings crédit agricole and the    crisisedit when the interbank lending market seized up crédit agricole was forced in january  to sell its longstanding stake in suez for € billion and then in may  to organise a € billion rights issue to which all the regional banks subscribed to meet basel ii regulatory requirements it also undertook a € billion programme of nonstrategic asset disposals at the end of  the government decided to loan france’s six largest banks € billion in two tranches at an interest rate of  to enable them to continue to play their role in the economy crédit agricole did not take part in the second tranche and repaid the government in october  crédit agricole’s crisis exit strategy was well received by the markets with the share price gaining more than  over  in  crédit agricole continued to report negative results posting a loss of around € billion in the third quarter the greek branch emporiki was separated from its profitable wealthy parts in albania bulgaria and romania which were integrated into the crédit agricole group the whole investment into emporiki cost around € billion the remaining greek part was sold off to alpha bank for € crédit agricole also withdrew totally from spanish bank bankinter resulting in a book loss of € million and took a massive € million writedown on consumer credit notably owing to difficulties in italy furthermore crédit agricole had to write down the goodwill on its balance sheet goodwill amounted to € billion in september  well above the actual value in early february  the bank announced that it would book € billion in writedowns and costs – a record amount according to the media getting back to fundamentals from edit in march  the crédit agricole group unveiled its mediumterm strategic plan which put the emphasis on retail banking insurance and saving internationally the group decided to refocus on its core markets starting with italy the group’s secondlargest market the crédit agricole group sold its bulgarian subsidiary to corporate commercial bank for € million on  april  crédit agricole sa crédit agricole nord and crédit agricole nordest announced that they would sell  of their stake in crelan sa a belgian bank created out of the merger of crédit agricole belgique and centea to caisses coopératives belges by june  corporate governanceedit crédit agricole has a threetier structure comprising the local banks the regional banks and their branches and equity investments and crédit agricole sa and its subsidiaries the local and regional banks are cooperative companies crédit agricole sa is a jointstock company crédit agricole is one of the leading cooperative companies in the world local banksedit the  local banks form the foundation of crédit agricole they have  million stakeholders december  who are both clients and owners of the share capital through ownership shares of the local banks in accordance with the cooperative governance principle the local banks hold the bulk of the capital of the regional banks at the annual general meetings of the local banks which attract around  participants every year the stakeholders appoint over  volunteer directors regional banksedit crédit agricole’s regional banks are cooperative entities and fullyfledged banks offering a wide range of financial products and services to their  million clients end they boast a network of some  branches and  atms plus more than  instore cash points which provide crédit agricole customers with basic banking services some regional banks have merged to improve their financial strength and competitiveness with the total number of regional banks falling from  to  between  and  preventing exclusion from banking services to prevent customers affected by a personal event such as a death or unemployment from being excluded from banking services  regional banks have set up point passerelle centres which provide a friendly ear mediation and support for clients looking for help to get out of a difficult situation caisse régionale du nordest first introduced the system in  promoting employment for people with disabilities through an association set up to promote the employment of people with disabilities within crédit agricole heca the crédit agricole regional banks devote resources to the recruitment integration and continued employment of disabled workers measures include workstation modifications transport facilities and training since a lack of training makes it harder for people with disabilities to get work crédit agricole has set up workstudy training programmes to enable people who have their high school diploma to receive postsecondary qualifications the goal was to recruit more than  disabled persons between  and end and by end more than  permanent contracts and  workstudy contracts had been signed former miss france runnerup sophie vouzelaud who has been deaf from birth is heca’s official ambassador promoting the cooperative model the regional banks help to promote the cooperative model locally through a variety of initiatives such as the perspectives mutualistes conference series pau in  angers in  reims in  orléans in  and by issuing special bank cards for stakeholders fédération nationale du crédit agricoleedit fédération nationale du crédit agricole fnca is the body through which the regional banks discuss policy express their views and represent themselves fnca plays the role of a trade body it is a forum for discussions that arise at the grassroots level and it plays a proactive guiding role it represents crédit agricole’s regional banks and the group with respect to the public authorities agricultural trade associations and bodies with authority for cooperative and mutual banking fnca provides services to regional banks particularly in the fields of vocational training through the crédit agricole mutuel training centre and human resource management the senior management team is represented by dominique lefebvre chairman of fédération nationale du crédit agricole philippe brassac secretary general of fédération nationale du crédit agricole bertrand corbeau ceo of fédération nationale du crédit agricole crédit agricole saedit new headquarters of crédit agricole sa in montrouge in  caisse nationale de crédit agricole was privatised becoming crédit agricole sa a public limited company owned by the regional banks and group employees in  crédit agricole sa was floated on the stockmarket although the regional banks  at the time retained a majority share as provided for by the group’s mutual articles of association senior management of crédit agricole sa chairman dominique lefebvre ceo philippe brassac board of directors the board is made up of members elected by the annual general meeting representatives of trade organisations members elected by employees a nonvoting member and a representative of the works council a complex structure the regional banks own  of crédit agricole sa which in turn holds  of their capital in the form of nonvoting cooperative securities certificats coopératifs dassociés an internal debate is continually underway on striking a balance between growing activities that serve the regional banks directly and promoting businesses that lie outside their sphere institutional investors particularly in the uk and us are not always at ease with this approach brand identityedit sloganedit  to  “le bon sens près de chez vous” common sense close to home  to  “le bon sens en action” common sense in action  to  “limagination dans le bon sens” “imagination guided by common sense”  to  “une relation durable ça change la vie” “a lasting relationship changes your life” since  “le bon sens a de l’avenir” “common sense has a future” visual identityedit  the first official logo conveying crédit agricole’s exclusive focus on the agricultural sector  crédit agricole adopts a second logo to express the firm’s strong involvement in the development of france  third logo combining the letters c and a  creation of the current logo which summarises the group’s desire to continue to move forward and to favour openness towards the outside world financial and market dataedit the cooperative investment certificates of  regional banks and the shares of crédit agricole sa the group holding company are listed on the paris stock exchange crédit agricole sa is also a member of the dow jones euro stoxx  sbf  euronext  aspi eurozone and ftsegood index crédit agricole group dataedit the crédit agricole group comprises all the local and regional banks crédit agricole sa and all their subsidiaries financial data in € million years            net banking income            net income group share            shareholders equity            crédit agricole sa group dataedit the crédit agricole sa group comprises the holding company crédit agricole sa as well as all its subsidiaries financial data in € million years            net banking income            net income group share            shareholders equity            sports sponsorshipedit cyclingedit crédit agricole team jersey in  following the tour de france crédit agricole became the lead sponsor of the cycling team led by roger legeay previously sponsored by gan an insurer the initial investment was frf  million a year over the years the team won many stages in major cycling races as well as several national championships in  crédit agricole reviewed its sports sponsorship strategy and ended its partnership after ten years main article crédit agricole cycling team rugbyedit crédit agricole has been the main sponsor of the italian national rugby team since  via its italian subsidiary cariparma main article italy national rugby union team controversiesedit this section does not cite any sources please help improve this section by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed march  learn how and when to remove this template message in september  credit agricole had to book a € million charge related to an unauthorized trading loss at its new york subsidiary on april   credit agricole revealed that it would post  billion in losses related to subprime mortgage securities in may  credit agricole sought to raise € billion in equity capital from its shareholders the shares controversially sold off from € to € over the successive period as the financial crisis escalated in may  credit agricole identified €billion of asset disposals including the banks  percent stake in italian bank intesa sanpaolo which was worth an estimated € billion the group purchased in august  empiriki bank for € billion which it later sold for one euro after suffering € billion of losses in the investment httpwwwvulpesinvestcomttmyghgrantttmyghpdf in  the french governments autorité de la concurrence the department in charge of regulating competition fined eleven banks including crédit agricole the sum of  euros for colluding to charge unjustified fees on check processing especially for extra fees charged during the transition from paper check transfer to exchanges checkimage electronic transfer see alsoedit paris portal companies portal european financial services roundtable referencesedit  a b c d e entire crédit agricole group including regional cooperative banks annual report  pdf crédit agricole retrieved  july    httpwwwforbescomcompaniescreditagricole  crédit agricole  la banque verte sengage à devenir arcenciel boursiercom  january  retrieved  august    a b c d e f g h i history of credit agricole group creditagricolecom creditagricolecom retrieved  august    a b c d e que de bon sens stratégiesfr  january  retrieved  august    décret du  février  relatif à lapplication de la loi du  août  sur le crédit mutuel et la coopération agricole legifrancegouvfr  january  retrieved  august    la croissance de l’entredeuxguerres pdf histoiredentreprisecom december  retrieved  august    a b c du monde rural à la bourse la longue marche du crédit agricole lesechosfr  july  retrieved  august    fiche de paul driant senatfr retrieved  august    répartition du capital de crédit agricole sa lamarquecom retrieved  august    lobsession du crédit aux pme lemondefr  january  retrieved  august    oui le bon sens a de lavenir  marquenemotypepadcom  october  retrieved  august    loi n°  du  janvier  relative à la mutualisation de la caisse nationale de crédit agricole legifrancegouvfr  december  retrieved  august    histoire de la société crédit agricole andlilcom  may  retrieved  august    banque lucien douroux le paysan conquérant lepointfr  june  retrieved  august    tagliabue john for a banker roots and reach nytimescom the new york times retrieved  august    fortune global  fortunecom retrieved  august    the global  forbescom retrieved  august    crédit agricole vend sa participation dans suez lefigarofr  january  retrieved  august    le crédit agricole nutilis