 crossborder transfers fx investment products interest rate hedging products and debt capital markets the company’s transaction banking services comprise liquidity and working capital management services trade finance services such as guarantees documentary transactions structured trade finance nonrecourse purchase of trade receivables and payable discounting as well as a suite of etrade and export and commodity finance services its debt optimization and distribution services comprise origination structuring and arrangement of syndicated and bilateral mediumterm and longterm loans and underwriting of primary and secondary distribution of syndicated loans to banks and nonbank institutional investors the company’s islamic banking services include strategic advice risk management and capital raising in addition it offers wealth management services to highnetworth and ultrahighnetworth clients the company was formerly known as calyon and changed its name to crédit agricole corporate and investment bank sa in february  the company was incorporated in  and is headquartered in montrouge france crédit agricole corporate and investment bank sa is a subsidiary of credit agricole sa detailed description  place des etatsuniscs montrouge  francefounded in  employees phone       wwwcacibcom key executives for crédit agricole corporate and investment bank sa mr jeanyves jose hocher chief executive officer age  mr frédéric méron head of finance eric lechaudel head of operations  country coos opc mr philippe brassac chairman of the board of directors and chief executive officer of crédit agricole s a age  mr françois marion deputy chief executive officer age  compensation as of fiscal year  crédit agricole corporate and investment bank sa key developments credit agricole cib global markets division appoints sebastien lafosse as head of retail and private banking group for the americas jul   credit agricole cib global markets division announced that it has appointed sebastien lafosse as head of retail and private banking group for the americas in his new role based in new york lafosse will report locally to stanislas varin head of cross asset structuring and koceila maames head of financial institutions sales americas he reports globally to regis benichou global head of retail and private banking group lafosse who has more than  years experience in retail distribution has most recently been at natixis sa heading the cross asset solutions distribution crédit agricole cib global markets division hires sebastien lafosse as head of retail and private banking group for the americas jul   crédit agricole cib global markets division hires sebastien lafosse as head of retail and private banking group for the americas sebastien brings more than  years experience in the retail distribution space starting his career at société générale as part of the latin american structured products distribution then on the retail structured product team at morgan stanley and most recently at natixis heading the cross asset solutions distribution crédit agricole cib hires two new strategists in new york jun   crédit agricole cib hires two senior strategists in new york alex li is appointed head of us rates strategy for the global markets research division in new york as head of us rates strategy for the global markets research division alex will develop interest rate research products in the us alex’s career in strategy spans more than two decades in the us covering a broad range of fixed income products with a focus on interest rates he reports globally to mohit kumar global head of rates strategy and locally to christine cremel global markets regional coo for the americas prior to joining crédit agricole cib alex was chief us treasury and inflation strategist at deutsche bank securities responsible for the development of clientfacing interest rate research products in treasuries inflationlinked and interest rate futures including strategy publications and quantitative models alex received his bs from the university of toronto and his ms from stanford university italo lombardi has joined crédit agricole cib as the latin america economist and strategist based in new york italo does economic and financial market analysis including macroeconomics politics fx and interest rates for the main economies of latin america he was the latin america economist and strategist for more than five years at standard chartered and previously at bnp paribas in new york he also worked at roubini global economics italo holds a ba in economics from ibmec business school in sao paulo brazil he reports globally to sebastien barbé head of emerging markets research  strategy and locally to christine cremel global markets regional coo for the americas similar private companies by industry company name region banque bia europe banque cin europe banque cooperative mutuelle nord europe banque descompte sa europe banque de lunion europeenne europe recent private companies transactions typedate target mergeracquisition november   credit agricole securities asia limited request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of sp global bloombergcom does not create or control the content for inquiries please contact sp global market intelligence directly by clicking here stock quotes market data is delayed at least  minutes company lookup most searched private companies company name geographic region lawyers committee for civil rights under law united states nyc inc united states the advertising council inc united states bertelsmann ag europe rush university united states sponsored financial commentaries sponsored links browse companies a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z              request profile update only a company representative may request an update for the company profile documentation will be required to contact crédit agricole corporate and investm